case_name_full: STATE of Missouri v. James DORSEY a/k/a Ronald Brackett
attorneys: Richard E. McFadin, F.A. White, Jr., and Thomas C. Fincham of McFadin & White, North Kansas City, Mo., for appellant., John Ashcroft, Atty. Gen., George Cox, Asst. Atty. Gen., Jefferson City, Mo., for respondent.

opinions.opinion_text:
PER CURIAM:
ORDER
This is a direct appeal from a jury conviction for robbery, first degree, in violation of § 569.020, RSMo 1978.
No jurisprudential purpose would be served by written opinion.
Judgment affirmed. All concur.
Rule 30.25(b).
